with
> a perfectly applied, ever so thin layer of sealent, brushed on if
necessary.
> Not in the VW air cooled world but some carb base gaskets with multiple
> drillings and ports are well served by a perfect layer of sealant for
instance
> to keep the ports from cross talking with each other, in the extreme case
ones
> where there are air passages and coolant passages in the carb flange
adjacent
> the actual intake port.
> YMMV.  It often doesn.
